The VE3RXR DMR Repeater is located in Little Current, On it is about 1300 ft above ground level and covers the Manitoulin Island & North Shore area including Lake Huron and the North Channel. It is a Motorola 8300 repeater running 25 watts and is connected to the Canda Wide talkgroup 4326 (3026).

This repeater is maintained by the Big Shanty Repeater Group. More information about BSRG repeaters, including sample codeplug files, can be found on our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/BigShantyRG/

As this is a Brandmeister repeater, all BM talkgroups are accessible on-demand by keying/"waking up" the TG from Time Slot 1. You are free to wake up any talkgroup on TS1, however we do recommend using the following guide when programming your radio for the most common talkgroups.

Radio Configuration Guide (Updated 2019-03-01):

Timeslot 1:
31131 - Metro Atlanta - Static (fault-tolerant, Bridged to K4USD)
3100 - USA (The Bridge) - PTT (Bridged to GeorgiaDMR/K4USD/DCI/etc)
91 - Worldwide - PTT
93 - North America - PTT
310 - TAC 310 - PTT (Bridged to K4USD/DCI/DMRX)
311 - TAC 311 - PTT (Bridged to K4USD/DCI/DMRX)
312 - TAC 312 - PTT (Bridged to K4USD/DCI/DMRX)
*Any other Brandmeister talkgroup can also be activated using PTT on TS1.

Timeslot 2 (Reserved for Local/GA traffic):
2 - Local Network - Static (bridged between all BSRG/W4KIP DMR repeaters, fault-tolerant, and linked to Brandmeister TG 311340 for hotspot access)
9 - Local Repeater - Static
3113 - GA Statewide - Static (Bridged to K4USD, fault-tolerant)

To test using the Parrot (repeats your audio back to you), make a private call to 9990 using your radio's direct dial/private call feature. When you finish transmitting, you should hear your voice played back to you after a few seconds.

Sweat Mountain high site repeater on K4USD network.

https://brandmeister.network/index.php?page=repeater&id=311340

This repeater is maintained by the Big Shanty Repeater Group. More information about BSRG repeaters, including sample codeplug files, can be found on our Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/BigShantyRG/

As this is a Brandmeister repeater, all BM talkgroups are accessible on-demand by keying/"waking up" the TG from Time Slot 1. You are free to wake up any talkgroup on TS1, however we do recommend using the following guide when programming your radio for the most common talkgroups.

Radio Configuration Guide (Updated 2018-10-01):

Timeslot 1:
31131 - Metro Atlanta - Static (Bridged to K4USD)
3100 - USA (The Bridge) - PTT (Bridged to GeorgiaDMR/K4USD/DMRX/etc)
91 - Worldwide - PTT
93 - North America - PTT
310 - TAC 310 - PTT (Bridged to K4USD/DCI/DMRX)
311 - TAC 311 - PTT (Bridged to K4USD/DCI/DMRX)
312 - TAC 312 - PTT (Bridged to K4USD/DCI/DMRX)
*Any other Brandmeister talkgroup can also be activated using PTT on TS1.

Timeslot 2 (Reserved for Local/GA traffic):
2 - Local Network - Static (bridged between all BSRG/W4KIP DMR repeaters, and linked to TG 311340 for hotspot access)
9 - Local Repeater - Static
3113 - GA Statewide - Static (Bridged to K4USD)

To test using the Parrot (repeats your audio back to you), make a private call to 9990 using your radio's direct dial/private call feature. When you finish transmitting, you should hear your voice played back to you after a few seconds.
